# 🚀 Running Context-Aware-Development Locally (Without Docker)

This project has **4 runnable components**. Here's how to run each one locally.

---

## Prerequisites

| Requirement | Version | Check Command |
|---|---|---|
| **Node.js** | ≥ 20 | `node -v` |
| **npm** | (bundled with Node) | `npm -v` |
| **Python 3** | ≥ 3.8 (for Platform) | `python --version` |

---

## 1️⃣ Core Engine / CLI (TypeScript — Root Project)

This is the main ContextOS CLI + SDK.

```powershell
# Step 1 — Install dependencies
npm install

# Step 2 — Build all packages (plugins → contracts → core-engine → orchestration → main)
npm run build

# Step 3 — Run the CLI in dev mode (uses tsx for hot-reload)
npm run dev
```

> [!TIP]
> You can also call CLI commands directly:
> ```powershell
> npm run cad -- <command>
> # Example:
> npm run cad -- ctx eval --suite docs/eval/suites/retrieval-core.yml
> ```

### Other Useful Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `npm test` | Build + run all Vitest tests |
| `npm run lint` | Run ESLint |
| `npm run format` | Run Prettier (auto-fix) |
| `npm run local:verify` | Run local verification script |

---

## 2️⃣ Platform Server (Python — `platform/`)

This is the **CodeForge AI** platform — a Python HTTP server running on port **8000**.

```powershell
# Step 1 — Navigate context (no cd needed, run from root)
# Step 2 — Run the server
python platform/main.py
```

The server starts at:
- 🌐 **UI**: `http://127.0.0.1:8000`
- 📖 **API Docs**: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs`
- 💚 **Health**: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/health`
- 🤖 **Agent API**: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/agent/state`

> [!NOTE]
> The platform uses Python's built-in `http.server` with no external pip packages required (it uses stdlib only).
> If you need AI features, set the `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable or configure it in [platform/config.toml](file:///c:/Users/RAVIPRAKASH/Context-aware-development-/platform/config.toml).

### Configuration

Edit [platform/config.toml](file:///c:/Users/RAVIPRAKASH/Context-aware-development-/platform/config.toml) to customize:
- Server host/port
- AI model settings
- Feature flags (enable/disable features)
- Rate limiting
- Plugin auto-loading

---

## 3️⃣ Cloud Web App (Next.js — `cloud/apps/web/`)

This is the **ContextOS Cloud** control plane (Next.js + Supabase + Stripe).

```powershell
# Step 1 — Install dependencies
cd cloud/apps/web
npm install

# Step 2 — Set environment variables (create a .env.local file)
# Required variables:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=<your-supabase-url>
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<your-supabase-anon-key>
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<your-service-role-key>
#   CONTEXTOS_INTERNAL_API_TOKEN=<any-secret-token>
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=<optional>
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=<optional>

# Step 3 — Run in dev mode
npm run dev
```

Runs at: `http://localhost:3000`

---

## 4️⃣ Cloud Worker (TypeScript — `cloud/apps/worker/`)

This is the background job processor for the cloud app.

```powershell
# Step 1 — Install dependencies
cd cloud/apps/worker
npm install

# Step 2 — Set environment variables
#   CONTEXTOS_WEB_URL=http://localhost:3000
#   CONTEXTOS_INTERNAL_API_TOKEN=<same-token-as-web>

# Step 3 — Run in dev mode
npm run dev
```

---

## 5️⃣ Documentation Website (Docusaurus — `website/`)

This is the project documentation site.

```powershell
# Step 1 — Install dependencies
cd website
npm install

# Step 2 — Run in dev mode
npm run start
```

Runs at: `http://localhost:3000` (default Docusaurus port)

> [!TIP]
> You can also run the website from the root directory:
> ```powershell
> npm run website:dev
> ```

---

## 6️⃣ VS Code Extension (TypeScript — `context-ide/vscode/`)

Build and package the ContextOS VS Code extension:

```powershell
# Build the extension
npm run vscode:build

# Package as .vsix (requires @vscode/vsce)
npm run vscode:package
```

The VSIX file will be created at `dist/contextos-vscode.vsix`. Install it in VS Code via:
```
Extensions → ⋯ → Install from VSIX...
```

---

## 🗺️ Quick Reference — All Commands at a Glance

| Component | Install | Run (Dev) | Port |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Core CLI** | `npm install` (root) | `npm run dev` | N/A (CLI) |
| **Platform Server** | None (stdlib Python) | `python platform/main.py` | `8000` |
| **Cloud Web** | `npm install` (in `cloud/apps/web`) | `npm run dev` | `3000` |
| **Cloud Worker** | `npm install` (in `cloud/apps/worker`) | `npm run dev` | `3001` |
| **Website** | `npm install` (in `website`) | `npm run start` | `3000` |
| **VS Code Ext** | N/A | `npm run vscode:build` | N/A |

> [!WARNING]
> The Cloud Web and Documentation Website both default to port `3000`. Run only one at a time, or configure a different port for one of them.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Minimum Local Setup**: If you just want the core ContextOS functionality, you only need:
> 1. `npm install` (root)
> 2. `npm run dev` (CLI)
> 3. `python platform/main.py` (Platform server)
